name: clouderrorreporting
title: Stackdriver Error Reporting API
description: Stackdriver Error Reporting groups and counts similar errors from cloud services. The Stackdriver Error Reporting API provides a way to report new errors and read access to error groups and their associated errors.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

schemas.name: ErrorContext
schemas.desc:
A description of the context in which an error occurred.
This data should be provided by the application when reporting an error,
unless the
error report has been generated automatically from Google App Engine logs.

fields.name: user
fields.desc:
The user who caused or was affected by the crash.
This can be a user ID, an email address, or an arbitrary token that
uniquely identifies the user.
When sending an error report, leave this field empty if the user was not
logged in. In this case the
Error Reporting system will use other data, such as remote IP address, to
distinguish affected users. See `affected_users_count` in
`ErrorGroupStats`.

fields.name: reportLocation
fields.desc:
The location in the source code where the decision was made to
report the error, usually the place where it was logged.
For a logged exception this would be the source line where the
exception is logged, usually close to the place where it was
caught. This value is in contrast to `Exception.cause_location`,
which describes the source line where the exception was thrown.

fields.name: httpRequest
fields.desc:
The HTTP request which was processed when the error was
triggered.

schemas.name: SourceLocation
schemas.desc:
Indicates a location in the source code of the service for which
errors are reported.
This data should be provided by the application when reporting an error,
unless the error report has been generated automatically from Google App
Engine logs. All fields are optional.

fields.name: lineNumber
fields.desc: 1-based. 0 indicates that the line number is unknown.

fields.name: functionName
fields.desc:
Human-readable name of a function or method.
The value can include optional context like the class or package name.
For example, `my.package.MyClass.method` in case of Java.

fields.name: filePath
fields.desc:
The source code filename, which can include a truncated relative
path, or a full path from a production machine.

schemas.name: ListGroupStatsResponse
schemas.desc: Contains a set of requested error group stats.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc:
If non-empty, more results are available.
Pass this token, along with the same query parameters as the first
request, to view the next page of results.

fields.name: timeRangeBegin
fields.desc:
The timestamp specifies the start time to which the request was restricted.
The start time is set based on the requested time range. It may be adjusted
to a later time if a project has exceeded the storage quota and older data
has been deleted.

fields.name: errorGroupStats
fields.desc: The error group stats which match the given request.

schemas.name: DeleteEventsResponse
schemas.desc: Response message for deleting error events.

schemas.name: ReportedErrorEvent
schemas.desc: An error event which is reported to the Error Reporting system.

fields.name: serviceContext
fields.desc: [Required] The service context in which this error has occurred.

fields.name: eventTime
fields.desc:
[Optional] Time when the event occurred.
If not provided, the time when the event was received by the
Error Reporting system will be used.

fields.name: context
fields.desc: [Optional] A description of the context in which the error occurred.

fields.name: message
fields.desc:
[Required] The error message.
If no `context.reportLocation` is provided, the message must contain a
header (typically consisting of the exception type name and an error
message) and an exception stack trace in one of the supported programming
languages and formats.
Supported languages are Java, Python, JavaScript, Ruby, C#, PHP, and Go.
Supported stack trace formats are:

* **Java**: Must be the return value of [`Throwable.printStackTrace()`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/Throwable.html#printStackTrace%28%29).
* **Python**: Must be the return value of [`traceback.format_exc()`](https://docs.python.org/2/library/traceback.html#traceback.format_exc).
* **JavaScript**: Must be the value of [`error.stack`](https://github.com/v8/v8/wiki/Stack-Trace-API)
as returned by V8.
* **Ruby**: Must contain frames returned by [`Exception.backtrace`](https://ruby-doc.org/core-2.2.0/Exception.html#method-i-backtrace).
* **C#**: Must be the return value of [`Exception.ToString()`](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.exception.tostring.aspx).
* **PHP**: Must start with `PHP (Notice|Parse error|Fatal error|Warning)`
and contain the result of [`(string)$exception`](http://php.net/manual/en/exception.tostring.php).
* **Go**: Must be the return value of [`runtime.Stack()`](https://golang.org/pkg/runtime/debug/#Stack).

schemas.name: TrackingIssue
schemas.desc: Information related to tracking the progress on resolving the error.

fields.name: url
fields.desc:
A URL pointing to a related entry in an issue tracking system.
Example: https://github.com/user/project/issues/4

schemas.name: ListEventsResponse
schemas.desc: Contains a set of requested error events.

fields.name: timeRangeBegin
fields.desc: The timestamp specifies the start time to which the request was restricted.

fields.name: errorEvents
fields.desc: The error events which match the given request.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc:
If non-empty, more results are available.
Pass this token, along with the same query parameters as the first
request, to view the next page of results.

schemas.name: ErrorGroupStats
schemas.desc:
Data extracted for a specific group based on certain filter criteria,
such as a given time period and/or service filter.

fields.name: count
fields.desc:
Approximate total number of events in the given group that match
the filter criteria.

fields.name: affectedUsersCount
fields.desc:
Approximate number of affected users in the given group that
match the filter criteria.
Users are distinguished by data in the `ErrorContext` of the
individual error events, such as their login name or their remote
IP address in case of HTTP requests.
The number of affected users can be zero even if the number of
errors is non-zero if no data was provided from which the
affected user could be deduced.
Users are counted based on data in the request
context that was provided in the error report. If more users are
implicitly affected, such as due to a crash of the whole service,
this is not reflected here.

fields.name: numAffectedServices
fields.desc:
The total number of services with a non-zero error count for the given
filter criteria.

fields.name: representative
fields.desc:
An arbitrary event that is chosen as representative for the whole group.
The representative event is intended to be used as a quick preview for
the whole group. Events in the group are usually sufficiently similar
to each other such that showing an arbitrary representative provides
insight into the characteristics of the group as a whole.

fields.name: timedCounts
fields.desc:
Approximate number of occurrences over time.
Timed counts returned by ListGroups are guaranteed to be:

- Inside the requested time interval
- Non-overlapping, and
- Ordered by ascending time.

fields.name: group
fields.desc: Group data that is independent of the filter criteria.

fields.name: firstSeenTime
fields.desc:
Approximate first occurrence that was ever seen for this group
and which matches the given filter criteria, ignoring the
time_range that was specified in the request.

fields.name: lastSeenTime
fields.desc:
Approximate last occurrence that was ever seen for this group and
which matches the given filter criteria, ignoring the time_range
that was specified in the request.

fields.name: affectedServices
fields.desc:
Service contexts with a non-zero error count for the given filter
criteria. This list can be truncated if multiple services are affected.
Refer to `num_affected_services` for the total count.

schemas.name: ErrorGroup
schemas.desc: Description of a group of similar error events.

fields.name: groupId
fields.desc:
Group IDs are unique for a given project. If the same kind of error
occurs in different service contexts, it will receive the same group ID.

fields.name: trackingIssues
fields.desc: Associated tracking issues.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The group resource name. Example: projects/my-project-123/groups/my-groupid

schemas.name: HttpRequestContext
schemas.desc:
HTTP request data that is related to a reported error.
This data should be provided by the application when reporting an error,
unless the
error report has been generated automatically from Google App Engine logs.

fields.name: method
fields.desc: The type of HTTP request, such as `GET`, `POST`, etc.

fields.name: remoteIp
fields.desc:
The IP address from which the request originated.
This can be IPv4, IPv6, or a token which is derived from the
IP address, depending on the data that has been provided
in the error report.

fields.name: referrer
fields.desc: The referrer information that is provided with the request.

fields.name: userAgent
fields.desc: The user agent information that is provided with the request.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: The URL of the request.

fields.name: responseStatusCode
fields.desc: The HTTP response status code for the request.

schemas.name: ErrorEvent
schemas.desc: An error event which is returned by the Error Reporting system.

fields.name: eventTime
fields.desc:
Time when the event occurred as provided in the error report.
If the report did not contain a timestamp, the time the error was received
by the Error Reporting system is used.

fields.name: context
fields.desc: Data about the context in which the error occurred.

fields.name: message
fields.desc: The stack trace that was reported or logged by the service.

fields.name: serviceContext
fields.desc: The `ServiceContext` for which this error was reported.

schemas.name: TimedCount
schemas.desc:
The number of errors in a given time period.
All numbers are approximate since the error events are sampled
before counting them.

fields.name: count
fields.desc: Approximate number of occurrences in the given time period.

fields.name: startTime
fields.desc: Start of the time period to which `count` refers (included).

fields.name: endTime
fields.desc: End of the time period to which `count` refers (excluded).

schemas.name: ServiceContext
schemas.desc:
Describes a running service that sends errors.
Its version changes over time and multiple versions can run in parallel.

fields.name: resourceType
fields.desc:
Type of the MonitoredResource. List of possible values:
https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/api/resources

Value is set automatically for incoming errors and must not be set when
reporting errors.

fields.name: version
fields.desc:
Represents the source code version that the developer provided,
which could represent a version label or a Git SHA-1 hash, for example.

fields.name: service
fields.desc:
An identifier of the service, such as the name of the
executable, job, or Google App Engine service name. This field is expected
to have a low number of values that are relatively stable over time, as
opposed to `version`, which can be changed whenever new code is deployed.

Contains the service name for error reports extracted from Google
App Engine logs or `default` if the App Engine default service is used.

schemas.name: ReportErrorEventResponse
schemas.desc:
Response for reporting an individual error event.
Data may be added to this message in the future.

methods.name: deleteEvents
methods.desc: Deletes all error events of a given project.

pathParams.name: projectName
pathParams.desc:
[Required] The resource name of the Google Cloud Platform project. Written
as `projects/` plus the
[Google Cloud Platform project
ID](https://support.google.com/cloud/answer/6158840).
Example: `projects/my-project-123`.

pathParams.name: groupName
pathParams.desc: [Required] The group resource name. Written as projects/projectID/groups/group_name. Call groupStats.list to return a list of groups belonging to this project. Example: projects/my-project-123/groups/my-group

methods.name: update
methods.desc:
Replace the data for the specified group.
Fails if the group does not exist.

pathParams.name: projectName
pathParams.desc: [Required] The resource name of the Google Cloud Platform project. Written as projects/ plus the Google Cloud Platform project ID. Example: projects/my-project-123.

optinalQueryParams.name: serviceFilter.version
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] The exact value to match against
[`ServiceContext.version`](/error-reporting/reference/rest/v1beta1/ServiceContext#FIELDS.version).

optinalQueryParams.name: alignmentTime
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] Time where the timed counts shall be aligned if rounded
alignment is chosen. Default is 00:00 UTC.

optinalQueryParams.name: serviceFilter.resourceType
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] The exact value to match against
[`ServiceContext.resource_type`](/error-reporting/reference/rest/v1beta1/ServiceContext#FIELDS.resource_type).

optinalQueryParams.name: timedCountDuration
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] The preferred duration for a single returned `TimedCount`.
If not set, no timed counts are returned.

optinalQueryParams.name: pageToken
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] A `next_page_token` provided by a previous response. To view
additional results, pass this token along with the identical query
parameters as the first request.

optinalQueryParams.name: pageSize
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] The maximum number of results to return per response.
Default is 20.

optinalQueryParams.name: order
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] The sort order in which the results are returned.
Default is `COUNT_DESC`.

optinalQueryParams.name: timeRange.period
optinalQueryParams.desc: Restricts the query to the specified time range.

optinalQueryParams.name: alignment
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] The alignment of the timed counts to be returned.
Default is `ALIGNMENT_EQUAL_AT_END`.

optinalQueryParams.name: serviceFilter.service
optinalQueryParams.desc:
[Optional] The exact value to match against
[`ServiceContext.service`](/error-reporting/reference/rest/v1beta1/ServiceContext#FIELDS.service).

methods.name: report
methods.desc:
Report an individual error event. This endpoint accepts either an OAuth token, or an API key for authentication. To use an API key, append it to the URL as the value of a `key` parameter. For example: 
POST https://clouderrorreporting.googleapis.com/v1beta1/projects/example-project/events:report?key=123ABC456
